The Bureau Chief of Voice of Nigeria for the South West, Elder Yinka Salaam has urged youths to shun cybercrime, ritual killings, cultism, drug abuse, and other inimical tendencies. Salaam spoke at a Career Mentorship Programme and Scholarship organised by Standard Bearers Islamic Organization held at Al Falaah Model College, Osogbo, Osun State. Salaam enjoined the students to be exemplary citizens of Nigeria and be good ambassadors of Islam, in deeds and words, wherever they find themselves. Abimbola Aisha of Al Jihad Group of Schools and Sulaiman Mutumaina were among the best students that performed excellently in the exam organised by the NGO. Speaking on behalf of the other 30 awardees, the duo of Abimbola Aisha and Sulaiman Mutumaina expressed gratitude to the organiser of the award.   Kwara Police Command nab suspected transborder kidnapper     Kaduna traffic official beats driver to death     Suspected killer of police chief arrested in Imo   - Advertisement - During the event, Standard Bearers Islamic Organization awarded Best Secondary School Students for their academic excellence. Some of the awardees got N20,000 each to enable them to pay for their West African Examinations Council and National Examination Council examinations. In his lecture, Salaam charged the youths to always be of good conduct, saying that their future lies in their hands and would largely be determined by their strength of character. Salaam urged them to abstain from anything that can serve as the clog in the wheel of their educational pursuit. He charged them on the need to be inquisitive in the pursuit of their education, “Ultimately, take care of your manners, behaviors, virtues – You are the Light of the World. You are His ambassadors”